<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-49-0610 </DOCNO><TEXT>If importers of substantial tonnages of US coal negotiate their own railroadcontracts, it could reduce costs and open up opportunities for new non-exportingUS producers. However, it does mean increased administrative burdensand upping the risk of coal loss in transit. Each shipper should thereforeget all of the facts available on this option before making decisionon contract negotiations. 1 photo.</TEXT></DOC>